# Slack MCP
Use `mcp-cli` to access Datadog Slack through the `slack` MCP server.

Config:
- Server: `slack`
- Endpoint: `https://mcp.slack.com/mcp`
- Proxy: `~/.pi/agent/skills/slack-mcp/scripts/slack-mcp-proxy.py`
- Auth: macOS keychain service `Claude Code-credentials`, account `$(whoami)`
- Client ID: `1601185624273.8899143856786`

Setup and auth:
```fish
python3 ~/.pi/agent/skills/slack-mcp/scripts/slack-mcp-auth.py
```

Discovery:
```fish
MCP_STRICT_ENV=false mcp-cli info slack
MCP_STRICT_ENV=false mcp-cli info slack slack_search_public_and_private
MCP_STRICT_ENV=false mcp-cli info slack slack_read_channel
MCP_STRICT_ENV=false mcp-cli info slack slack_read_thread
```

Common read-only calls:
```fish
MCP_STRICT_ENV=false mcp-cli call slack slack_search_public_and_private '{
  "query": "search terms",
  "limit": 10,
  "include_context": true,
  "response_format": "markdown"
}'

MCP_STRICT_ENV=false mcp-cli call slack slack_search_channels '{
  "query": "channel-name",
  "limit": 10,
  "response_format": "markdown"
}'

MCP_STRICT_ENV=false mcp-cli call slack slack_read_channel '{
  "channel_id": "CHANNEL_ID",
  "limit": 20,
  "response_format": "markdown"
}'

MCP_STRICT_ENV=false mcp-cli call slack slack_read_thread '{
  "channel_id": "CHANNEL_ID",
  "message_ts": "MESSAGE_TS",
  "limit": 50,
  "response_format": "markdown"
}'
```

Write calls require explicit user approval:
```fish
MCP_STRICT_ENV=false mcp-cli call slack slack_send_message_draft '{
  "channel_id": "CHANNEL_ID",
  "message": "draft text"
}'
```

Rules:
- Prefer read-only tools: search, read channel, read thread, read user profile.
- Do not send, schedule, create, update, or react unless the user explicitly asks.
- Prefer `slack_send_message_draft` over `slack_send_message` when drafting is enough.
- Slack MCP uses the user's normal Slack permissions and all access may be logged.
- Do not print or persist Slack access or refresh tokens.
- If auth fails, rerun `slack-mcp-auth.py` and retry.
